article.description: — Justus Jackson had 18 points in UT Martin's 104-76 season-opening victory over Champion Christian on Monday night.
article.headline: UT Martin earns 104-76 victory over Champion Christian
article.linkText: UT Martin earns 104-76 victory over Champion Christian
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- — Justus Jackson had 18 points in UT Martin's 104-76 season-opening victory over Champion Christian on Monday night. Jackson shot 8 for 13, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc for the Skyhawks. Jacob Crews scored 16 points and added five rebounds. Jalen Myers had 15 points and was 5 of 9 shooting and 4 of 4 from the free throw line. Ariyon Williams led the Tigers in scoring, finishing with 22 points, five assists and four steals. KJ Younge added 20 points for Champion Christian. In addition, Damian Bohlman had nine points. NEXT UP UT Martin's next game is Saturday against Mississippi State on the road. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
